parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Passlock anti-theft system can cause the vehicle to not start, leaving the driver stranded, which can be a safety issue, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the security lock dash light flashes
the security system will not allow the vehicle to start
the vehicle requires a 10-minute wait before restarting
the key in ignition goes to accessory mode but fails to turn over
all indicator lamps on the dash display
and the door chime sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to turn off while driving, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine turns off while driving
the vehicle will not stay in the run position
the ignition switch moves out of the run position due to the weight on the keyring or road conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various issues, including brake light and cruise control failure, which can lead to accidents or reduce vehicle safety.
symptoms: Brake lights and cruise control fail to function
the fuse box needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ECM can cause the vehicle to not start, which can leave the driver stranded, and can also cause engine misfire and reduced power.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the "Service Stab Sys Traction Fault" message is displayed
engine misfire
engine light comes on
and reduced power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking dashboards can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, potentially leading to airbag malfunction or explosion in the event of a collision, which can cause injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Dashboard cracks
especially around airbag attachment points
with no apparent reason other than using unprotected plastic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag malfunction can cause injuries or fatalities, and in this case, the airbag caught fire, leading to additional harm.
symptoms: Airbag explosion
fire
and injuries (head
ankle
shoulder
and burns) in a collision.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rusting and cracking of the rear subframe can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, leading to potential loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Visible rust or corrosion on the rear subframe
cracks or breaks in the rear subframe
exposed wiring or cables
hanging parking brake cable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and fragmentation of the dashboard can lead to potential injuries in the event of a crash, as sharp plastic fragments can become projectiles and cause harm to occupants.
symptoms: Cracks or breaks in the dashboard
raised safety concerns for occupants in the event of a crash
potential for sharp plastic fragments to become projectiles.
